  "title": "Mary Colter's Buildings at Grand Canyon - Grand Canyon National Park (U.S. National Park Service)",
  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_830326\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_2049669_830326\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481855\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_2049669_481855\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Mary Colter's Buildings at Grand Canyon</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6273768\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<p>Mary Colter was the chief architectural designer and interior decorator for the Fred Harvey Company from 1902 to 1948. Her creative free-form buildings at Grand Canyon took direct inspiration from the landscape and served as part of the basis of the developing artistic aesthetic for appropriate development in areas that became national parks.<br/>\n<br/>\nShe designed eight unique Grand Canyon Buildings. (All are still in use today). Hopi House, Hermit's Rest, Lookout Studio, Phantom Ranch, Desert View Watchtower, Bright Angel Lodge, and the two Fred Harvey employee dormitories, Colter Hall and Victor Hall. (Now dormitories for Xanterra employees).<br/>\n<br/>\nTo protect Mary Colter's work, four of her buildings at Grand Canyon (Hopi House, Lookout Studio, Hermit's Rest, and Desert View Watchtower) were declared National Historic Landmarks in 1987.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_2049671\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_2049671\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-right\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/images/MJCat50-16951.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Full length photo of Mary Colter sitting in an elaborate wicker chair that wraps around her.\" src=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/images/MJCat50-16951.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"Architect Mary Colter at 50 years old.\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Architect Mary Colter at age 50 </figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>Mary Elizabeth Jane Colter</h3>\n<p>Mary Colter was born in Pittsburgh in 1869 and grew up in Texas, Colorado, and St. Paul, Minnesota. While attending the California School of Design in San Francisco she apprenticed in an architect's office and then went into teaching back in St. Paul.<br/>\n<br/>\nThrough informal contacts with the Fred Harvey Company, Colter eventually landed a job as interior designer of the Indian Building adjacent to the Santa Fe's new Alvarado Hotel in Albuquerque, along the main line. Although the Mission Revival style had been popular in California since the 1890s, the Alvarado Hotel and its adjacent Indian Building (both destroyed) were the first of their kind in New Mexico. Her reputation swiftly grew, and her use of natural materials in forms that mimicked nature served as the basis for later work by architect Herbert Maier and others who designed what we now term \"rustic\" architecture.<br/>\n<br/>\nAs a full-time architectural designer/decorator in the Fred Harvey Company, Mary Colter would design and oversee the construction of eight buildings on the South Rim of Grand Canyon National Park in Arizona. Colter was a perfectionist, who spent a lifetime advocating and defending her aesthetic vision in a largely male-dominated field. In 1948, at the age of 79, Colter officially retired from the Fred Harvey Company. On January 8, 1958, at the age of 88, Mary Elizabeth Jane Colter died.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6273761\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6273761\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h4>Explore A Park Map</h4>\n<p>Explore all of Mary Colter's buildings on the interactive map below. To learn more information about a site click on the images below the map or a number on the map. Zoom in to see a site or area more clearly.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6273758\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6273758\"></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5501117\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5501117\">\n<div class=\"Component FeatureGrid\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_hermits_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_hermits_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"An stone arch structure with a bell on the top.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/18783EBC-C14A-F946-C4A0424FFFD5E75F.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/18783EBC-C14A-F946-C4A0424FFFD5E75F.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/18783EBC-C14A-F946-C4A0424FFFD5E75F.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Hermit's Rest History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Hermit's Rest provided a place for visitors to rest when traveling on the Fred Harvey Company’s sightseeing tours.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_lookout_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_lookout_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A stone building with the Grand Canyon in the background.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B08DA52-DDC0-8C59-6A2DB1DD045825AC.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B08DA52-DDC0-8C59-6A2DB1DD045825AC.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B08DA52-DDC0-8C59-6A2DB1DD045825AC.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Lookout Studio History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Inspired by the natural landscape around her, Mary Colter modeled this building after southwestern Native American architectural styles.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_ba_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_ba_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A group of people standing outside the entrance of a hotel\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A7A219C-F19C-82EC-99748A8342120A8B.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A7A219C-F19C-82EC-99748A8342120A8B.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A7A219C-F19C-82EC-99748A8342120A8B.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Bright Angel Lodge History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Fred Harvey Company built the Bright Angel Lodge on the former site of the Bright Angel Hotel and Camp established  by James Thurber.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_hopih_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_hopih_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A adobe pueblo building with two signs in the front.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C7574F6-D736-0BA3-B1381C13A9164064.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C7574F6-D736-0BA3-B1381C13A9164064.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C7574F6-D736-0BA3-B1381C13A9164064.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Hopi House History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Hopi House pays tribute to the Hopi and their ancestors that have inhabited the Grand Canyon for centuries. </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_phantom_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_phantom_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A stone cabin halfway blocked by a tree showing fall leaves.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/1890094F-9952-A5DF-A6354D911F651139.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/1890094F-9952-A5DF-A6354D911F651139.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/1890094F-9952-A5DF-A6354D911F651139.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Phantom Ranch History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Only accessible by mule, by foot, or by rafting the Colorado River, Phantom Ranch is the only lodging facility below the canyon rim. </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/mary-colter---indian-watchtower.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/mary-colter---indian-watchtower.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A stone\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/18A0C69E-9BDD-5F9C-0F7D49877451658C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/18A0C69E-9BDD-5F9C-0F7D49877451658C.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/18A0C69E-9BDD-5F9C-0F7D49877451658C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Desert View Watchtower History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Modeled after Ancestral Puebloan dwellings found at Hovenweep and Mesa Verde, the Desert View Watchtower opened in 1932.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: April 4, 2022</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
